    "actions_taken": [
      "HM transported to lower deck and reported incident to pilot",
      "HM examined by facility medic",
      "HM transported via motor vessel to shore base",
      "HM transported via ambulance to Lafayette General Medical Center",
      "Lessee discontinued helicopter mechanics rotation on offshore facilities",
      "All aircraft maintenance moved to onshore operations"
    ],
    "summary": "On February 11, 2019 at 1640 hours, a helicopter mechanic fell while attempting to retrieve grease guns from the top of helicopter N438PH. The mechanic had recently purchased oversized work boots online that did not fit properly. While standing on a 2.5\" x 4\" helicopter fold-out step and holding a pitch change link, the mechanic's left foot slipped due to the boot folding inward. The mechanic lost grip and fell backwards, striking the boarding step and heliport deck. A grease gun subsequently fell and struck the mechanic's face. The mechanic sustained a broken coccyx, broken nose, and an 8-stitch laceration above the right eye. The mechanic was wearing a safety helmet and safety glasses which reduced injury severity.",
